Integration with Existing Pantheon Concepts

This meshes well with ideas you’ve developed:

* Signalying: each signal contributes a differential element to the accumulated semantic field.
* Tracer Dye: inject a small signal and observe how the semantic volume changes to infer hidden structure.
* Recall Navigation: compressed semantic volumes can be rehydrated when new context arrives.
* Checksum/Zoro: verify that reconstruction preserves the intended invariant rather than merely matching surface words.
* Pinecone: preserve compressed semantic seeds until enough context exists to reconstruct the larger volume.

The overarching idea is that Pantheon becomes less a system for storing sentences and more a system for preserving and translating semantic invariants across different representations. Words, images, code, stories, equations, or rituals become different surfaces generated from the same underlying “volume” of meaning. That perspective naturally supports both compression (store the invariant rather than every instance) and translation (map one surface realization to another while preserving the underlying structure).